{"artefact":[["_response_info",{"status":"ok"}],["title","Workplace temperatures"],["id","https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/workplace-temperatures.json"],["web_url","https://www.gov.uk/workplace-temperatures"],["format","answer"],["details",{"need_id":"200","business_proposition":false,"alternative_title":"","overview":"There is no law for a minimum or maximum temperature, but during working hours the temperature in all workplaces inside buildings must be reasonable\r\n","updated_at":"2012-10-09T18:06:52+00:00","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>During working hours the temperature in all indoor workplaces must be reasonable.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s no legal minimum or maximum, but guidance suggests a minimum of 16\u00baC (or 13\u00baC if employees are doing physical work). </p>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s no maximum temperature limit.</p>\n\n<p>Employers must stick to health and safety at work law, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>keeping the temperature at a comfortable level</li>\n  <li>providing clean and fresh air</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Employees should talk to their employer if the workplace temperature isn&rsquo;t comfortable.</p>\n"}],["tags",[{"title":"Business premises and business rates","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/business%2Fpremises-rates.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes the business rates calculator, leases and renting","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=business%2Fpremises-rates","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business/premises-rates"},"parent":{"title":"Business","id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/tags/business.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Information about starting up and running a business in the UK, including help if you're self employed or a sole trader.","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://contentapi.production.alphagov.co.uk/with_tag.json?tag=business","web_url":